cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.CC, cs.IR, cs.CG

Reasoning: 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is the most likely category as the paper presents a new algorithm for approximate circular string matching.
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is also likely as the problem of approximate string matching involves combinatorial and discrete mathematical concepts.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is another possible category as the paper discusses the time and space requirements of the algorithm.
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is a less likely category, but still possible as approximate string matching is used in text search and information retrieval applications.
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is also a less likely category, but possible as the problem of approximate string matching can be viewed as a geometric problem of finding points within a certain distance from a given point or set of points.
